summary: you know, with the amount of times crowley and aziraphale go out to eat (they don't always go out together, even), i'm beginning...
body:
you know, with the amount of times crowley and aziraphale go out to eat (they don’t always go out together, even), i’m beginning to think that neither of them ever learnt to cook, presumably because they don’t technically need to. but what about once they’ve got that cottage in the south downs? it’s a bit of a ways away from all their favorite spots in london, so unless they’ve got teleportation powers we didn’t see over the course of the story, going out would have to become a rare treat. (this is all assuming, of course, that their place at the south downs is more of a permanent residence and not just a vacation home)

i was thinking, would they make an effort to figure it out? would they miracle the food perfect? for personal reasons i’d like to think aziraphale might have a number of recipe books in his collection, and they’d occasionally make a night, morning, afternoon, whatever of it and to be quite honest neither of them are exactly.. competent when it comes too cooking. crowley likes to talk big about being able to chop vegetables very quickly (mostly to tease aziraphale, who doesn’t enjoy the fact that crowley has the tendency to wave the knife around when he’s talking particularly animatedly), but when things go awry he gives the recipe book (and the food) pep talks not unlike the ones his houseplants are usually on the receiving end of. aziraphale is of the opinion that there are too many steps that go into all of it, but he develops a better appreciation for the well-cooked food he’s been such a fan of for just over six millennia.

at any rate, eventually crowley figures out that he’s actually not bad at baking. he decides on the year anniversary of preventing armageddon that it would be nice to surprise aziraphale with a devil’s food cake (chosen purposefully for the name). the cake is amazing, aziraphale is both touched and impressed, a not-so-secretly pleased with himself crowley decides that he should try this baking thing more often, and the rest is history.

summary: I really want more discussion about the scene in the first few minutes of the pilot of good omens, where Aziraphale shelters...
body: I really want more discussion about the scene in the first few minutes of the pilot of good omens, where Aziraphale shelters Crowley with his wing. Cause like. Pure?? Cute?? Sweet?? Gay??? But also, like, why did he? When we hear the thunder and the rain, Crowley just kind of steps closer and Aziraphale lifts his wing automatically. They’ve theoretically never met, but Crowley just seems to know that Zira will do that, and Zira seems more than willing enough to do so. So instant husbands, shall we agree?

excerpt: An Archive of Our Own, a project of the Organization for Transformative Works
description:
Crowley talks to the Bentley, in the way some people talk to plants or their pets. After a particularly painful fight between he and his angel, he takes it for a drive.

or

I realize how much I talk to my car on long drives, and wondered if Crowley would do the same. And what would happen to a car that had been driven by a supernatural entity for almost 100 years. And then out came a little story about Crowley and Aziraphale from the Bentley’s point of view

Crowley talks to the Bentley, in the way some people talk to plants or their pets. After a particularly painful fight between he and his angel, he takes it for a drive.
